solution:
**3 collections**: `people` (for both `Voice Actor` and `Writer`, discriminated by a `role` field, since they are both `Person` subtypes with small, non-overlapping extra attributes), `books`, and `cartoons`.

- **`Write` (Book 1:1 : Writer 1:N)** — each book has exactly one writer, so **embed** a writer summary sub-document directly inside the book document (denormalized, avoids a join for the common "who wrote this book" read).
- **`Inspired` (Cartoon 0:1 : Book 0:N)** — each cartoon is inspired by at most one book, so **embed a reference** (`book_id` + a few denormalized fields) inside the cartoon document.
- **`Plays` (Cartoon N:N Voice Actor, attribute `character_name`)** — a many-to-many relationship, so it is **referenced** as an array of sub-documents (`{voiceActorId, name, character_name}`) inside the cartoon document; this keeps "who voices this cartoon" a single read, at the cost of updating the array if a voice actor's cached name changes.

```json
// books collection
{
  "_id": "b1",
  "name": "The Orange Girl",
  "number_volumes": 1,
  "publication_date": "1994-09-01",
  "writer": { "writerId": "w1", "name": "Bill", "surname": "Smith", "birth_date": "2001-05-10" }
}

// cartoons collection
{
  "_id": "c1",
  "title": "Adventures",
  "language": "English",
  "original": true,
  "number_episodes": 26,
  "season": 1,
  "inspiredBy": { "book_id": "b1", "name": "The Orange Girl" },
  "cast": [ { "voiceActorId": "va1", "name": "Mark", "character_name": "Hero" } ]
}

// people collection
{ "_id": "va1", "personal_id": "P1", "name": "Mark", "role": "voiceActor", "voice_type": "low", "nationality": "Japanese" }
{ "_id": "w1", "personal_id": "P2", "name": "Bill", "role": "writer", "birth_date": "2001-05-10" }
```

```javascript
db.cartoons.aggregate([
  { $match: { "inspiredBy.book_id": { $exists: true, $ne: null } } },
  { $lookup: {
      from: "books",
      localField: "inspiredBy.book_id",
      foreignField: "_id",
      as: "book"
  } },
  { $unwind: "$book" },
  { $match: { "book.writer.name": "Mark" } },
  { $project: {
      title: 1,
      totalVoiceActors: { $size: "$cast" }
  } }
])
```

Each cartoon's `inspiredBy` sub-document points to a book; `$lookup` joins that book, we filter by the embedded writer's name, and `$size` on the `cast` array gives the number of voice actors for that cartoon.

```javascript
db.cartoons.aggregate([
  // N.B. explicitly require the cartoon to actually be inspired by a book
  { $match: { "inspiredBy.book_id": { $exists: true, $ne: null } } },
  { $lookup: {
      from: "books",
      localField: "inspiredBy.book_id",
      foreignField: "_id",
      as: "book"
  } },
  { $unwind: "$book" },
  { $match: { "book.publication_date": { $gt: ISODate("2020-03-17") } } },
  { $lookup: {
      from: "people",
      localField: "cast.voiceActorId",
      foreignField: "_id",
      as: "castDetails"
  } },
  { $match: { "castDetails.nationality": "Japanese" } },
  { $group: {
      _id: "$book._id",
      bookName: { $first: "$book.name" },
      totalCartoons: { $sum: 1 }
  } }
])
```

The first `$match` on `inspiredBy.book_id` is the mandatory "actually inspired by a book" guard called out in the N.B.; skipping it would also count cartoons with no book at all and lose points.

```javascript
db.cartoons.aggregate([
  { $match: { "inspiredBy.book_id": { $exists: true, $ne: null } } },
  { $lookup: {
      from: "books",
      localField: "inspiredBy.book_id",
      foreignField: "_id",
      as: "book"
  } },
  { $unwind: "$book" },
  { $match: {
      "book.number_volumes": { $gte: 10 },
      "book.writer.name": "Bill",
      "book.writer.birth_date": { $gt: ISODate("2000-10-10") }
  } },
  { $unwind: "$cast" },
  { $group: {
      _id: "$cast.voiceActorId",
      voiceActorName: { $first: "$cast.name" },
      totalCartoons: { $sum: 1 }
  } }
])
```

"was born after 10/10/2000" refers to the writer (the last-mentioned subject in the sentence), so the birth-date filter is applied to the embedded `book.writer.birth_date`, not to the voice actor.
